        <svcproc svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="2">
            <title>SERVICE PROCEDURE</title>
            <svcsubproc>
                <title>Remove</title>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Remove blower motor. Refer to GROUP 16-CAB-AIR CONDITIONING in the CTS-5000 Master
                        Service Manual for information on removing the blower motor assembly, for the model vehicle
                        being serviced.
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Disconnect the electrical connector and ground wire from the old blower motor (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9516031">Figure 1</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f9516031" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G9516031.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 1.</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Remove the vent tube from the blower motor (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9516031">Figure 1</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Remove the blower motor five (5) mounting screws (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9516031">Figure 1</hotlnk>) and remove the blower motor assembly from the
                        vehicle.
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Remove the blower wheel from the motor.</para>
                </step1>
            </svcsubproc>
            <svcsubproc>
                <title>Install</title>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Install the blower on the new motor.</para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Plug the electrical connector removed from the old blower motor into the pig tail on
                        the new blower motor (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9516032">Figure 2</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f9516032" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G9516032.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 2.</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Install the blower motor assembly (with new motor) in the heater or heater-A/C unit.
                        Install and tighten the five (5) mounting screws (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9516032">Figure 2</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Install the ground lead removed from the old blower motor, along with the ground
                        lead pig tail extending from the new blower motor (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9516032">Figure 2</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                    <specpara>
                        <note>
                            <para>If a heavy duty motor is being replaced, pull the power and ground leads out of the
                                new motor and discard. Pull both the power and ground wires out of the old motor and
                                plug them into the new motor. Be sure to match the wire color to the color of the plug
                                on the motor (
                                <hotlnk xrefid="f9516032">Figure 2</hotlnk>). If the leads are reversed, the motor will
                                run backwards. Install the ground lead under one of the unit mounting screws.
                            </para>
                        </note>
                    </specpara>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Install the blower motor vent.</para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Test for operation.</para>
                </step1>
            </svcsubproc>
        </svcproc>
